<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-08-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="229" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d229">
                    <head>No. 229.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName></hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-08-16"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 16, 1888</date>.
                            (Received October 8.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 686.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that the imperial
                        board of astronomy has reported that the third day of the second month of
                        next year (March 4, 1889) is an auspicious day for the assumption of
                        government by the Emperor in person.</p>
                    <p>That day has accordingly been fixed by the imperial decree for this
                        ceremony.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles
                            Denby.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>